* FreeSans, FreeMono, FreeSerif: http://savannah.nongnu.org/projects/freefont/

These fonts are covered by the GPL.

* 7th: 7th Service Truetype Font for Windows

2002 Iconian Fonts - Daniel Zadorozny

http://www.iconian.com/

This font comes with the following 10 versions: Regular, Italic, Leftalic, Outline, Outline Italic, Expanded, Extra Bold, Expanded Italic, Condensed, Semi-Condensed.
This font has several alternate characters in the upper and lower cases.
This font may be freely distributed and is free for all non-commercial uses.  This font is e-mailware; that is, if you like it, please e-mail the author at:
iconian@aol.com

* DejaVu: http://dejavu.sourceforge.net/

Fonts are (c) Bitstream (see below). DejaVu changes are in public domain.

* Loma: ftp://linux.thai.net/pub/ThaiLinux/software/thai-ttf/

Updated version of ftp://ftp.nectec.or.th/pub/NECTEC/fonts/Loma.tar.gz



